>NAME

if_nametoindex - convert network interface name to index

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <net/if.h>
	
	unsigned int if_nametoindex(const char *ifname);

>DESCRIPTION

This function returns the index of the network interface named by 'ifname'.

>RETURN VALUE

This function returns the index corresponding to the network interface named 'ifname'. If no such interface is found, this function returns 0 and sets [errno.6] to *ENXIO*.

>ERRORS

On error, this function returns 0 and sets [errno.6] to one of the following:

\* *ENXIO* - no interface named 'ifname' exists.

